Sao Paulo state to sell CPFL whole - report . Sao Paulo state governor Mario Covas said the state ' s soon - to - be - privatized power utility Companhia Paulista de Forca e Luz ( CPFL ) will be sold as a whole , Gazeta Mercantil financial newspaper reported Tuesday . Previously , the state said the company would be split into two units , one for generation and another for distribution , the paper said . CPFL , which is expected to be the first Sao Paulo state power firm to be privatized , is likely to be sold in late October or early November , Gazeta said . ( ( - - Fatima Cristina , Sao Paulo newsroom 5511 2485412 ) ) 
